<subSubSection id="C300A1C27958FF94BEA67CEBCADCFAE6" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497958FF94BEA67CEBCAF1FCC6" blockId="1.[151,641,766,792]" box="[151,641,766,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="D0ED45257958FF94BEA67CEBCAF1FCC6" bold="true" box="[151,641,766,792]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7958FF94BEA67CEBCAF1FCC6" bold="true" box="[151,641,766,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7958FF94BEA67CEBC9A0FCC6" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[151,464,766,792]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7958FF94BEA67CEBC9A0FCC6" bold="true" box="[151,464,766,792]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Macrostomus ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497958FF94BEA67D5DCADCFAE6" blockId="1.[151,1436,840,1645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
This group of species is characterized by face slightly wider at ventral margin; one pair of stout ocellar setae; flagellum tri-segmented; setae of the thorax: 3–4 dorsocentrals; 1 postpronotal; 1 supra-alar presutural (absent only in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7958FF94BEC57D80C9D7FC70" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[244,423,917,942]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7958FF94BEC57D80C9D7FC70" box="[244,423,917,942]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 0 supra-alar postsutural; 1 postalar; 1 notopleural posterior stout and 2 weak; 1–2 pair(s) of scutellars; 3–5 antepronotals; 1–3 tiny proepisternals and 3–5 katatergitals. Hind tibia with 2–7 long dorsal setae and first hind tarsomere with 1–7 long dorsal setae. Male wing lightly infuscated, nearly hyaline (except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7958FF94BEC57A1CC9D4FBFC" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[244,420,1033,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7958FF94BEC57A1CC97CFBFC" box="[244,268,1033,1058]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7958FF94BF2A7A1CC9D4FBFC" box="[283,420,1033,1058]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7958FF94BF837A1DC984FBFC" bold="true" box="[434,500,1032,1058]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D93207958FF94BF837A1DC984FBFC" box="[434,500,1032,1058]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
); costal cell and apical patch brown; pterostigma darker; veins M 
<subScript id="179EF00C7958FF94BAC57A0CCC8CFBF9" attach="right" box="[1268,1276,1049,1063]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript id="179EF00C7958FF94BB157A0CCD5CFBF9" attach="left" box="[1316,1324,1049,1063]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">2</subScript>
and apex of A 
<subScript id="179EF00C7958FF94BEFC7A56C8A5FB8F" attach="left" box="[205,213,1091,1105]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">1</subScript>
evanescent (rarely M 
<subScript id="179EF00C7958FF94BFE87A56C991FB8F" attach="left" box="[473,481,1091,1105]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript id="179EF00C7958FF94BC067A56CA4FFB8F" attach="left" box="[567,575,1091,1105]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">2</subScript>
distinct); cell dm elongate, blunt. Male terminalia with tergite 8 closely associated with sternite 8, projected and prolonged distally, with apex acute or blunt. Epandrium with small anterodorsal break and no anteroventral sinus; anterodorsal and posterodorsal protuberances of subequal height or posterodorsal higher than anterodorsal protuberance. Hypandrium slender, rather narrow, generally with distinct setae basally and pair of distal protuberances. Cercus divided into two lobes (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B8FB87958FF94BA827AC5C8ACFACF" author="Rafael &amp; Cumming" firstAuthor="Rafael" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="439 - 448" refId="ref9452" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2004). The Neotropical genera Macrostomus Wiedemann and Porphyrochroa Melander (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). Revista brasileira de Zoologia 21, 439 - 448." type="journal article" year="2004">Rafael &amp; Cumming 2004</bibRefCitation>
), anterior cercus somewhat elongate and posterior cercus with a membranous or sclerotized protuberance. Phallus as long as hypandrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300A1C27958FF94BEF47B51CB4CF9B3" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497958FF94BEF47B51CB4CF9B3" blockId="1.[151,1436,840,1645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
Female. Frons as wide as or slightly wider than anterior ocellus width. Face from one third to almost as large as width of anterior ocellus. Legs with or without pinnate scales on hind tibia dorsally, rarely present ventrally. Wing distinctly more infuscated and wider than in male or approximately of same width. Terminalia usually less shining and more gray pruinose than preabdomen. Tergite 8 elongate, wider at base and with distal sinus (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7958FF94BF187BCAC9F1FA27" box="[297,385,1503,1529]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1698,1722]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,296,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-189@12.[151,1436,274,1672]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrostomus flavus, n. sp., paratypes from Roraima. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–L, female; F, hindleg, posterior view; G, wing; H, distal abdominal tergites, dorsal view with right setae omitted; I, distal abdominal segments, lateral view; J, distal abdominal sternites, ventral view with left setae omitted; K–L, genital fork in lateral and ventral view; M, spermathecae. Scales: F = 0.5 mm; B–C,E,H–J = 0.2 mm; K–M = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321590/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 6h</figureCitation>
). Sternite 8 higher laterally on posterior third and ventrally with two less sclerotized spots at distal one quarter (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7958FF94BF967813CA56F9FE" box="[423,550,1542,1568]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1698,1722]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,296,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-189@12.[151,1436,274,1672]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrostomus flavus, n. sp., paratypes from Roraima. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–L, female; F, hindleg, posterior view; G, wing; H, distal abdominal tergites, dorsal view with right setae omitted; I, distal abdominal segments, lateral view; J, distal abdominal sternites, ventral view with left setae omitted; K–L, genital fork in lateral and ventral view; M, spermathecae. Scales: F = 0.5 mm; B–C,E,H–J = 0.2 mm; K–M = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321590/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Figs. 6i–j</figureCitation>
). Genital fork sclerotized, rather simple, sometimes with short lateral projections (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7958FF94BF057839C9C8F998" box="[308,440,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1698,1722]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,296,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-189@12.[151,1436,274,1672]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrostomus flavus, n. sp., paratypes from Roraima. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–L, female; F, hindleg, posterior view; G, wing; H, distal abdominal tergites, dorsal view with right setae omitted; I, distal abdominal segments, lateral view; J, distal abdominal sternites, ventral view with left setae omitted; K–L, genital fork in lateral and ventral view; M, spermathecae. Scales: F = 0.5 mm; B–C,E,H–J = 0.2 mm; K–M = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321590/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Figs. 6k–l</figureCitation>
). Genital chamber membranous with small sclerotized areas. Spermatheca with relatively long duct and rather rounded capsule (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7958FF94BCFF7846CB5FF9B3" box="[718,815,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1698,1722]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,296,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-189@12.[151,1436,274,1672]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrostomus flavus, n. sp., paratypes from Roraima. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–L, female; F, hindleg, posterior view; G, wing; H, distal abdominal tergites, dorsal view with right setae omitted; I, distal abdominal segments, lateral view; J, distal abdominal sternites, ventral view with left setae omitted; K–L, genital fork in lateral and ventral view; M, spermathecae. Scales: F = 0.5 mm; B–C,E,H–J = 0.2 mm; K–M = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321590/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7958FF94BD347846CB5FF9B3" box="[773,815,1619,1645]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" unit="m" value="6.0">6m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
